<span class="header1">Outdoor paired with Arts/Communications (AB)</span>

<p>An "AB" person loves to work in the open environment in settings such as nature (nature photographer), entertainment (marching band), recreation (tennis coach), animals (wildlife guide), and land improvements (landscaper) and is able to communicate well. The word "communicate" means that you can get your ideas, thoughts, or feelings understood by others easily and clearly through speaking or writing. With this pattern, you will probably want to share your interest in nature, the environment, or animals with others through your communications skills.</p>
<p>Often, an "AB" person communicates well through "visual media" using pictures, charts, graphs, or diagrams to help others understand. No matter which method you decide to use to communicate, others will probably be able to understand you.</p>
<p>Most occupations in this pairing require a Bachelor's Degree or specialized training. Higher levels of education such as a Master's Degree or a Ph.D. are valuable to certain occupations in this pattern.</p>

<p><strong>Here are some career possibilities for you to explore:</strong></p>

