<span class="header1">ARTS AND COMMUNICATIONS</span>
<p>Do you want to share your interest in nature and the environment with others?  Do you have strong communication skills?  If so, a career as an environmental lawyer, writer, or photographer may be of interest to you.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Environmental Lawyer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AB/1360.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Environmental Lawyer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you want to influence how people and organizations use the earth's environment, this occupation may be for you. To practice environmental law, you must understand the law and communicate well. You must also be organized and able to negotiate with others. If you become an environmental lawyer, you might develop a legal case or appear in court to prevent the building of a road through a wilderness area.  You might also defend a logging company's right to build that road.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You will need a Bachelor's Degree and three years of law school to be an environmental lawyer. You must also pass the state "bar exam."  To learn about nature sciences and city and rural development, volunteer with political action groups concerned about the environment.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>Environmental lawyer salaries range from $44,000 to $145,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Writer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AB/1040.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Writer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like to write and are good at it, you may want to become a professional writer. Writers express their thoughts and ideas through words written on a page or computer screen. As a writer, you could help inform others about issues that affect the environment. You may work on nature documentaries, or on articles for newspapers, nature magazines, or scientific journals.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Employers look for writers with at least a Bachelor's Degree. Education is very valuable, but you must have talent and skill too. You will want to write as much as possible. Getting involved in writing groups, school newspapers, and yearbooks can give you valuable experience and improve your skills. Practice is important, so take every opportunity to write.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A writer's salary can range from $29,000 to $60,000 a year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Nature Photographer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AB/43060.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" ALT="Nature Photographer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like taking pictures of natural settings and have a good "eye,"  you may become a nature photographer. To do so, you must be creative and understand how cameras work. Your work might appear in magazines, books and journals, or in travel and advertising displays. Many photographers work for themselves. So, it is helpful to understand how a small business works.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A Bachelor's Degree in photography or the visual arts can develop your basic skills. But, you also need to be creative to succeed in this	field. Spend as much time as possible looking at great pictures and taking your own. Getting involved in photography clubs and working in photo shops and labs will help you learn more about using your camera to capture nature.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A nature photographer's salary ranges from $15,000 to  $50,000 per year.</blockquote>

